date-released: "2026-06-21"
abstract: >
  Public J2C result checkpoint for Deep Origin Theory. The release preserves
  the sequence from the earlier structural pre-execution lock through the first
  no-admission execution, the exact finite J2R representative lock without
  galaxy fitting, and the J2C rerun that produced a coefficient-only
  total-scaling no-go for that representative. It does not retire all J2, does
  not decide nonlinear K plus braiding, and does not claim MOND/QUMOND family
  defeat or final cosmic closure.
